JOHANNESBURG – A popular soccer administrator linked to one of the country’s top teams was arrested for speeding, Road Traffic Management Corporation (RTMC) said on Sunday. The 68-year-old was arrested in Nelspruit, Mpumalanga when he was allegedly driving his Mercedes Benz AMG at 175-km per hour in a 120-km zone. “Conduct of this senior official is completely unacceptable particularly when considering the high number of soccer players who die on the roads every year,” RTMC said in a statement.  READ: Pirates player arrested for speeding The official has been released on bail and is expected to appear in court soon. eNCA